<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_76c8e517-4c20-4cd2-90a3-a47d19268130" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="TAS"><sptc>C4D10</sptc><title id="_c5795383-144d-4a87-8da5-0a219a25f36d">Straining pits</title><archive-num>2019: H202.4c</archive-num><subclause id="_227d89b5-d9f3-4227-a27c-bbea4c0e87df" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_7b176dbb-ad6b-4d5d-9517-4e510cbfa5bd">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The straining pit must be connected and authorised by the Permit Authority.</p></subclause><subclause id="_92753203-356e-4540-97c3-2d71533b46ea" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_ae8b7810-9166-450b-8f58-dc5b60d23612">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The straining pit basket must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_a559ec75-8d01-44a7-a3e9-1322c411558e">be constructed of mild steel wire with a minimum diameter of 2.5 mm woven to give 7 mm aperture widths on a 32 mm x 32 mm x 25 mm angle iron frame with mitred corners; or </li><li id="_3f95dd3f-1ff9-4035-b48b-d979528e9f65">be constructed from minimum 3 mm thick mild steel plate, with 6 holes at 12 mm centres over the entire area of the basket; and</li><li id="_f60c08d1-e6b7-45b4-b4e6-304d2e3f5a88">be hot dipped galvanised after fabrication.</li></ol></subclause><callout id="_e375547f-76cd-452c-8798-08f3dfa9c033"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>See <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/7751_0.3.0.xml#_3dc53f4b-0b56-4d5f-a336-a1ca99730727" id="_34c5dcb3-c104-4d80-aa13-ada437a7e228" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">TAS Figure C4D10</xref> for a typical straining pit.</p><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/7751_0.3.0.xml" id="_3dc53f4b-0b56-4d5f-a336-a1ca99730727" variation="TAS"><num/><title id="_166d5f49-da2c-4ee4-80ed-6d5619cc2645"/></image-reference></callout></clause>